<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
	<!-- Base Info.plist: Xcode merges its GENERATE_INFOPLIST_FILE keys (scene manifest, launch
	     screen, icons, bundle keys) on top of this. We only declare what generation can't: the
	     ATS exception that lets the WKWebView (https web.stremio.com) reach the embedded streaming
	     server at http://127.0.0.1:11470 (cleartext loopback), otherwise it shows "Error". -->
	<!-- Allow plain-http connections. The user can point the app at their OWN streaming server (a
	     dedicated box, a Tailscale host, a LAN machine) via Settings, and that URL is unknown at build
	     time, so a per-domain ATS exception isn't possible. CRITICAL: this must be the ONLY ATS key.
	     On iOS 10+, NSAllowsArbitraryLoads is IGNORED when NSAllowsLocalNetworking or
	     NSAllowsArbitraryLoadsInWebContent is also present, so those are deliberately removed; arbitrary
	     loads is a superset that already covers loopback, LAN, web content, and Tailscale's
	     100.64.0.0/10 range (issue #58). The app only talks to add-on endpoints and the server the user
	     configured. -->
	<key>NSAppTransportSecurity</key>
	<dict>
		<key>NSAllowsArbitraryLoads</key>
		<true/>
	</dict>
	<!-- iOS 14+ also gates reaching a host on the local network behind a privacy permission, separate
	     from ATS. A custom server on the home LAN (192.168.x / 10.x) trips it; declaring the usage
	     string lets iOS present and grant that permission instead of failing silently. Tailscale rides
	     a tunnel, not the LAN, so it does not trip this gate, which is why the Tailscale server already
	     connected without it (issue #58). No effect for embedded-server users (loopback is exempt). -->
	<key>NSLocalNetworkUsageDescription</key>
	<string>VortX connects to the streaming server you point it at, such as one you run at home on your local network or reach over Tailscale.</string>
	<!-- Schemes the "Play in another app" handoff queries with canOpenURL, so it can offer the
	     external players that are actually installed (Infuse, VLC). Without these, canOpenURL
	     always returns false and no direct-handoff buttons ever appear. -->
	<key>LSApplicationQueriesSchemes</key>
	<array>
		<string>infuse</string>
		<string>vlc-x-callback</string>
		<string>vlc</string>
		<string>outplayer</string>
		<string>senplayer</string>
		<string>nplayer-stremiox</string>
		<string>mxplayer</string>
	</array>
	<!-- Keep audio playing (and, crucially, the in-process streaming server thread alive) when the
	     screen locks or the app briefly backgrounds during playback. Without this, iOS suspends the
	     whole process: the embedded node server freezes (event-loop lag of minutes in the logs) and
	     the stream dies when you return. Pairs with the player's AVAudioSession(.playback) setup. -->
	<key>UIBackgroundModes</key>
	<array>
		<string>audio</string>
	</array>
</dict>
</plist>
